## Epic 2 — Player Search

### US-003 · Search for a player by name
**Priority:** P0

> As a casual fan, I want to search for any NBA player by name, so that I can quickly find someone I'm thinking of without knowing their exact full name.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Typing a partial name (e.g. "curry") and pressing Enter or clicking Search returns matching players.
- [ ] Results show: full name, position, height, weight, and team.
- [ ] A loading spinner appears while the request is in flight.
- [ ] If no matches are found, a clear empty state is shown (not a blank table).

**Edge cases:**
- Very common names (e.g. "James") return multiple players — all are listed.
- Retired players with no current team show "—" in the team column.

---

### US-004 · Browse paginated search results
**Priority:** P0

> As a casual fan, I want to page through search results, so that I can find the right player when there are many matches.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Results are shown 25 at a time.
- [ ] "Next" and "Previous" buttons navigate between pages.
- [ ] "Previous" is disabled on the first page.
- [ ] "Next" is disabled when there are no more results.

---

### US-005 · Navigate to a player's profile
**Priority:** P0

> As a fan, I want to click on a player's name in search results, so that I can open their profile and explore their statistics.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Clicking a player name or "Stats →" link opens the player detail view.
- [ ] The detail view shows the player's name prominently.
- [ ] A back button returns the user to the search results without re-running the search.

