## Epic 3 — Player Profile & Season Averages

### US-006 · View season averages for a player
**Priority:** P0

> As an amateur analyst, I want to see a player's season averages for any season in NBA history, so that I can understand their performance across their career.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] A season selector lists every NBA season from 1946–47 to the current season, newest first.
- [ ] Clicking "Load" fetches and displays averages for the selected season.
- [ ] Stats displayed: PTS/G, REB/G, AST/G, STL/G, BLK/G, TO/G, FG%, 3PT%, FT%, MIN/G, GP.
- [ ] Each stat is shown in a clearly labelled card.

**Edge cases:**
- If the player has no data for the selected season (e.g. they were not active), a "No data available" message is shown — not an error.
- FG%, 3PT%, and FT% are displayed as percentages (e.g. 47.3%), not decimals (e.g. 0.473).

---

### US-007 · View per-game stats for a player in a season
**Priority:** P0

> As an amateur analyst, I want to see individual game logs for a player in a selected season, so that I can spot performance trends and outlier games.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Game log shows the 10 most recent games for the selected season.
- [ ] Columns: date, PTS, REB, AST, STL, BLK, FG%, 3PT%, MIN, +/-.
- [ ] Dates are formatted as YYYY-MM-DD.
- [ ] The game log loads at the same time as season averages (parallel fetch).

**Edge cases:**
- If fewer than 10 games exist for the season, all available games are shown.
- If no game data exists, a "No game log available" message is shown.

---

### US-008 · Switch between seasons on a player profile
**Priority:** P1

> As an analyst, I want to change the selected season on a player's profile and reload their stats, so that I can compare performance across different years.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Changing the season selector and clicking "Load" replaces the stats with the new season's data.
- [ ] A loading state is shown while the new data loads.
- [ ] The previous season's data is cleared immediately when the new request begins.

