## Epic 5 — Games Browser

### US-011 · Browse game results by season
**Priority:** P0

> As a fan, I want to look up game results from any NBA season, so that I can revisit historical matchups and scores.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Season selector covers all NBA seasons from 1946–47 to present.
- [ ] Clicking Search fetches and displays games for the selected season.
- [ ] Each row shows: date, matchup (away @ home), final score, season, and game type.
- [ ] 25 games are shown per page with next/previous navigation.

**Edge cases:**
- Games that have not yet been played show "—" in the score column instead of 0–0.
- Very old seasons (pre-1970s) may have limited data; this is expected behaviour and not surfaced as an error.

---

### US-012 · Filter games by playoff or regular season
**Priority:** P0

> As a fan, I want to filter games to show only playoff games, so that I can focus on the postseason results I care about.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] A dropdown allows the user to choose "Regular season" or "Playoffs".
- [ ] Playoff games are visually tagged with a distinct label.
- [ ] Switching between types and re-searching returns only the correct game type.

---

### US-013 · Filter games by team
**Priority:** P1

> As a fan, I want to type a team name to filter the results, so that I only see games involving my favourite team.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] A text field accepts a team name or abbreviation (e.g. "Lakers", "LAL").
- [ ] Filtering is applied client-side against the fetched page of results.
- [ ] If no games match the filter, an empty state message is shown.

**Edge cases:**
- Matching is case-insensitive.
- Partial matches work (e.g. "lak" matches "Los Angeles Lakers").

---

### US-014 · Page through game results
**Priority:** P0

> As a user, I want to navigate through multiple pages of game results, so that I can browse beyond the first 25 entries.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] "Next" loads the next page of results.
- [ ] "Previous" returns to the prior page.
- [ ] Buttons are disabled appropriately at the start and end of the result set.
- [ ] Page position is preserved when navigating back from a game detail (if applicable in future).

