## Epic 6 — Error Handling & Edge Cases

### US-015 · See a clear error when the API is unreachable
**Priority:** P1

> As a user, I want to see a helpful error message when the API fails, so that I know whether the issue is with my key, my connection, or the service itself.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] A 401 response updates the status badge to "error" and suggests checking the key.
- [ ] A 429 (rate limit) response shows a message like "Too many requests — wait a moment and try again."
- [ ] Network errors (no connection) show "Could not reach the API. Check your connection."
- [ ] Errors are shown inline near the relevant section, not as page-level alerts.

---

### US-016 · Recover gracefully from an empty response
**Priority:** P1

> As a user, I want to see a clear empty state rather than a blank screen when a search returns no results, so that I know the app is working and I simply need to refine my query.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- [ ] Empty player search shows: an icon and "No players found. Try a different name."
- [ ] Empty season averages show: "No averages found for [name] in [season]."
- [ ] Empty game results show: "No games found. Try adjusting your season or filters."

