## Definition of Done

A story is considered done when:

1. All acceptance criteria are met and verified.
2. Edge cases have been tested manually.
3. The feature works on Chrome, Firefox, and Safari (current versions).
4. The feature renders correctly on both mobile (375 px) and desktop (1280 px+) viewports.
5. No console errors are introduced.
6. Error states and empty states are implemented alongside the happy path.
